In Bach's time, there were no world tours.
Beethoven, Brahms, Bartok, Enescu were people who worked, who were artists and not commercial representatives.
For me, organizing concerts, festivals, tours, releasing albums, they are all great, extraordinary, but as long as they are done in the service of music.
If not, we're in a system where creativity suffers, it has no freedom.
To illustrate this phenomenon, David Grimal gave the example of Romanian products before and after joining the European Union: "In Romania, before entering the EU, you had good vegetables and meat".
