A total of 62% of respondents said they were 'very satisfied' and 'satisfied' with the overall quality of their relationship.
"However, 18% show themselves as 'slightly dissatisfied' and 'very dissatisfied' in the couple relationship, and another 18% declare 'appropriate'", is the conclusion of the study, as shown in a statement released on Tuesday, Ziare.com.
The situation is slightly different when the responses of men and women are analysed separately.
Thus, 28% of men are very satisfied, 39% satisfied, 17% adequate, 6% very dissatisfied and 8% slightly dissatisfied.
For women, 33% were satisfied, 24% very satisfied, 8% very dissatisfied, 14% slightly dissatisfied and 19% picked the right category.
When we look at satisfaction, we see that men are more satisfied.
As for the neutral state, we see a difference of two percent.
"Similarly, in the very dissatisfied situation, the largest difference was in the slightly dissatisfied response where we see a difference of 6 percent", the statement said.
The study also showed that a quarter of Romanians (26%) spend an hour or even less time together, 18% spend between five and eight hours together, and 45% between two and four hours.
The authors of the study also say that "Romanians feel they need something more adventure in their lives (24%), followed by affection (21%), money (21%), safety (20%), new (19%), sex (19%), respect 18%, trust 17%, pleasure 17%, connection 17%, knowledge 16%, protection 14%, importance 14%, learning 12%, freedom 11%, self-knowledge 10% and control 7%".
The study was conducted by Extreme Training between June 1 and September 1 on 1,369 people, with a calculated margin of error of 2.6%.
