The rare disease from which a man suffers
American Nick Hess was suspected by his family of being an alcoholic, his wife even filming him when he was drunk, he could barely stand and his words were hard to understand.
Although the 35-year-old said he had not consumed alcohol, he was visibly intoxicated.
When she first accused me of being drunk when I wasn't, I thought she was crazy.
"But friends and family thought 'maybe he drinks alone, he's a secret alcoholic'", he said, according to the Mirror.
When he saw his wife's videos of him, the man from Columbus, Ohio, simply didn't recognize himself: "I was looking into my own eyes and I wasn't there".
'It was awful, I couldn't remember anything.'
In addition, his wife, who, although she doubted him for a while, eventually went with him to countless doctors, remembers that Nick's breath also smelled of alcohol.
The most sobering moment for Nick was when, after a minor car accident, he was found to have a blood-alcohol level three times the legal limit, even though he had only had one beer the night before.
After years and countless investigations, it was discovered that Nick was suffering from an extremely rare disease, "Auto-brewery syndrome".
Basically, his body makes all the carbohydrates he consumes ferment, turning them into alcohol.
The one who suspected that this might be Nick's illness was the wife herself.
There's no cure for the disease yet, but since he stopped eating carbs, Nick hasn't had any more episodes like this.
