Adventures in the stone age
According to the president of FRH, Alexandru Dedu, Romania can host a major handball competition only in 2024, and the preparation of the women's national handball team for qualifying for the Olympic Games costs a fortune.
The president of the Romanian Handball Federation, Alexandru Dedu, said yesterday, in a meeting with the press, that it is a great pride that our country has three teams in the Champions League groups.
As for the Romanian women's national handball team, "the main objective is to qualify for the Olympic Games in Rio, but for this they have to go through two stages of caudine forks, first the World Championship and second the prequalification tournament", Dedu said.
We really want to qualify for the Olympics.
There are some fantastic demands from the technical staff led by Tomas Ryde.
Staff that will consist of seven or eight people.
He wants an assistant coach, a doctor, two masseurs, goalkeeping coach, physical trainer, head of delegation.
They asked us to qualify for things, specifically physical training materials, that we'd never heard of.
These are all to get to the Olympics, and I will do everything in my power to have them.
We're talking about a massive investment, a lot of money.
But that's the way to do performance.
Because right now we're in the Stone Age of preparation.
"The teams we are fighting have these materials and have had them for some time", said Dedu, who mentioned that they are trying to obtain the necessary amounts to purchase these products from MTS and COSR.
The President of FRH also referred to the infrastructure in Romania and the possibility for our country to host a major handball competition.
We don't have a hall in Bucharest.
It's an infrastructure issue, and it's shameful that a European gymnastics championship is being questioned.
Let's not forget that in other parts of the world, entire Olympic districts have been built in the space of two years.
Before 1992, the current Olympic site in Barcelona was a garbage dump, and now it has become a beacon of beauty.
The same happened in London, where the 2012 Olympic Games were also a success in terms of investment.
"In my vision, in 2024 we can host a major competition", Dedu said.
He added that international handball bodies are willing to grant Romania the organisation of a major competition.
It's a priority for me to bring major handball competitions to Romania.
Mr. Puss went in with a civil project, the people agreed in principle, but it became clear very quickly that the hall would never be built.
And I had discussions with the EHF, I told them that we want, that we are able to organize and they agreed to invite them to the first match in the new arena in Bucharest and then we discuss concretely.
