New courses of Japanese culture organized at "Al.I. Cuza" University
You can learn about flower arrangement in a vase, ink painting, but also a light study of the fine arts specific to the Land of the Rising Sun at courses organized by students from Iasi.
The Japanese Culture Students' Circle in Iasi is organizing new courses of Japanese culture (ikebana, sumie and fine arts) between October 2015 and June 2016, courses for both beginners and advanced people.
These will take place at the Centre for European Studies of "Al. I. Cuza" University in Iasi and are organised to promote traditional and modern Japanese arts and culture.
For these there is a single participation fee of 50 lei per month per person.
In addition to art lessons, participants will be able to take part in exhibitions and other cultural activities promoting beauty.
The Japanese culture courses that I have proposed to you have been conceived as an invitation, addressed to the general public, to take the first steps on the road to self-knowledge through art.
